netstat: Network Statistics
	options:
		-t: tcp
		-u: udp
		-p: process ID (PID)
		-a: all
		-n: numaric address
		-l: listening port
To check port status:
	netstat -an | grep <port_num>

To llist all the TCP v6 ports:
	netstat -6at

To identify number of connections on a given port or IP:
	netstat -putan | grep <port/IP>

To view the routing table:
	netstat -r

To get the list of all the interfaces:
	netstat -i

To see the stats of protocol:
	netstat -s

